	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Since there seems to be so much sonfusion with<BR>
getting this wand, I would like to clarify some<BR>
things with you all.<BR>
 &lt;&lt; -- + Stats on the wand + -- &gt;&gt;<BR>
(( 5 Damage, 25 Delay, [2]Charges of Strip Enchantment-the powerful cancel magic spell<BR>
[+3] INT, [+3]Armor Class.))<BR>
 &lt;&lt; -- + How to get the wand (four parts) + --&gt;&gt;<BR>
1. Start off in Lesser Faydark, get a group and kill<BR>
Faerie Guards. There are about [7] Guards that spawn in the<BR>
Faerie camp (not the tower). The guards range from level [19 to 24]<BR>
If you are infact a young wizard, find a group - or maybe check the Mistmoore<BR>
zone to see if anyone wants to help you out. [For the 2x woven silk, dropped by Faerie Guards]<BR>
{Directions - From coming out of Castle Mistmoore, head left to the Faerie camp.<BR>
If you get lost, do a shout and ask for the location of the camp.}<BR>
2. The Sceptre. The Sceptre is in Castle Mistmoore, it is located in<BR>
the Grave Yard (aka GY). When you get to the GraveYard, you will see<BR>
a big temple looking structure in the center. Make sure you have Levitate [Level 24<BR>
Wizard Spell, can be purchased in Kelethin Druid Guild] on so that you dont fall through <BR>
the pit traps in the temple. The flower that you need in order to get the sceptre is on the<BR>
right hand side,[inside] the temple. Once you have the flower, [exit aka leave] the temple<BR>
and walk behind it. By this time, you should see a named Shadowgal, called Ssynthi.<BR>
[Hail Ssynthi] She will tell you to give her the flower, in return, you will receive the sceptre.<BR>
{Location: From Greater Faydark, head to Lesser Faydark -Right before the wizard teleport structure-<BR>
and once you are in Lesser Faydark, head either Left or Right, until you reach a druid circle. When you<BR>
arrive at the druid circle, you should also see a wide passage that leads into Castle Mistmoore.}<BR>
3. The Bloodback Wand. The Bloodback wand can be found on Greater Skeletons [level unknown, cons BLUE to me at level 30]<BR>
Greater Skeletons can be found all over the zone of Rathe Mountains. If you have a good group, you might want to also try<BR>
the skeleton tower[looks like the mummy tower that you may have seen in West Commons when you hunted dervish cutthroats]<BR>
Unfourtanetly, since the greater skeletons are located all throughout the zone, I can not give you specifics on where exactly<BR>
to find the wand.[Note: The Bloodback wand can be found on 1/3 (one out of three) skeletons in the Rathe Mountains.<BR>
{Directions: North Karanas, head into South Karanas, hug the zone wall on your right hand side[assuming that you are on the<BR>
North to South Karanas bridge] You will follow the wall for about [5] minutes until you come upon a part, where it [looks like a<BR>
zone entrance ~ Leads to Lake Rathetear] Once inside Lake Rathetear, walk down past the Gnoll camp (You'll see about 13 Gnolls) and onto the bridge.<BR>
If you dont like to [swim], use Levitate (Mentioned Above) and go left until you come upon another bridge. This can take [2 - 3] minutes. After you find the bridge<BR>
turn youself, facing land and head strait. You will encounter another zone point. [You] are now about to enter the Rathe Mountains.}<BR>
4. The Silverey Wand. (This wand says [Enchanter only, but it IS the correct wand for this quest.) This wand can be found in the<BR>
Lost Temple of Cazic Thule. It is dropped off silvered guards, near the [Pyramid - Not the 4 corners]. Silverd Guards Range from [level 25-28 (approx)]<BR>
You [will] need a group in order to get this wand (assuming you arent over level 39, so that none of this will [agro...attack] you.<BR>
{Directions - From Cazic Thule, head past the two double doors in the entrance and walk strait, until you reach another set of double doors.<BR>
Open the door to the right, and head down the hallway. You will need to have your entire party [invis]((Level 16 Wizard spell!)). Once you reach the<BR>
end of the hallway, open the door, and you will be in a small [maze]. Simple solution, head strait until you see the pyramid. On your way there, you will see<BR>
a circle of [lizard men, usually defenders (level 24+)] if you see this cirlce, with about [7] lizard men, continue strait..and you will be at the pyramid. [You see this<BR>
before you get to the pyramid, not after]. Kill some spawns, until you see a silver guard. They (the guards) are not rare by any chance and will spawn with the wand fairly often.}<BR>
===<BR>
This by far is not a complete guide on how to get the Wand, but I sure hope it helps you out.<BR>
If you see any errors that you'd like to correct, just do a post for it! :-). I, myself, own<BR>
the Weeping Wand, and I consider it a pretty good weapon for the caster [wizards].<BR>
Goodluck getting a Weeping Wand.<BR>
- + Written by, Aenamien Dvinngence<BR>
Level [31] Wizard, (Rallos Zek-PvP)
			</font>
	
		</td>
